<subSubSection id="D5EEACEA6A54FF98FF28F3D2095AFF30" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="574" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9D4BFF616A54FF98FF28F3D2095AFF30" blockId="1.[151,1436,1930,2027]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="574" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">
<emphasis id="AF8023736A54FF9BFF28F3D20C7BF822" bold="true" box="[151,273,1930,1955]" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing 
<quantity id="5A0C52846A54FF9BFE30F3D30C92F822" box="[399,504,1931,1955]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9-10 mm</quantity>
in male, 
<quantity id="5A0C52846A54FF9BFDD8F3D30FC1F822" box="[615,683,1931,1955]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
in female. 
<taxonomicName id="5AF484E26A54FF9BFC90F3D40EB2F823" box="[815,984,1930,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Katha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata">
<emphasis id="AF8023736A54FF9BFC90F3D40EB2F823" box="[815,984,1930,1955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">D. immaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="5AF484E26A54FF9BFBCBF3D40CF6F847" authority="Dubatolov, Kishida &amp; Wang, 2012" authorityName="Dubatolov, Kishida &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Danielithosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="AF8023736A54FF9BFBCBF3D4087DF823" box="[1140,1303,1931,1955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">D. fuscipennis</emphasis>
Dubatolov, 
<bibRefCitation id="F96582906A54FF9BFF28F3F60CF6F847" author="Kishida" box="[151,412,1966,1991]" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" refString="Dubatolov, V. V., Kishida, Y. &amp; Min, W. (2012) New records of lichen-moths from the Nanling Mts., Guangdong, South China, with description of new genera and species (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae: Lithosiinae). Tinea, 22, 1, 35 - 39." type="book chapter" year="2012">Kishida &amp; Wang, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the former can be distinguished by the following aspects: in the male genitalia, the left sacculus in 
<taxonomicName id="5AF484E26A54FF9BFEA7F38C0CD4F86B" box="[280,446,2002,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Katha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata">
<emphasis id="AF8023736A54FF9BFEA7F38C0CD4F86B" box="[280,446,2002,2027]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">D. immaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is narrower than that of 
<taxonomicName id="5AF484E26A54FF9BFD70F38C0E04F86B" box="[719,878,2003,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Danielithosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="AF8023736A54FF9BFD70F38C0E04F86B" box="[719,878,2003,2027]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">D. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the vesica has 7 thorn˗like cornuti and nearly 20 teeth˗like ones, whereas there are two cone˗shaped cornuti in the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
